LAGOS – Operatives of the Intelligence Response Team (IRT) of the Force Intelligence Bureau (FIB) have arrested a suspected notorious and serial fake bank alert fraudster, Olaogun Babatunde, for allegedly using fake bank alert to defraud a victim of N5million and another N4.6 million for the purchase of laptop computers. Olaogun, 37, from Ogbomosho, Oyo State, is a 2008 graduate from the University of Lagos. Popularly called ‘Evil Genius’ by his friends due to his expertise in generating fake bank credit alert, which he used to defraud traders and others, was previously arrested by the IRT, led by DCP Tunji Disu, when he commanded the Rapid Response Squad of the of the Lagos State Police Command in 2018. Then suspect then was alleged to have generated and used fake bank alert to buy laptop computers worth N4.6 million from a dealer one Kevin Otenuga.